# Strategy Implementation Rules

## Every Strategy Must
1. Inherit from `backend.strategies.base.BaseStrategy`
2. Accept `VolContext` in `generate_signals()` — all thresholds adapt to volatility
3. Return `list[TradeSignal]` from `backend.models.schemas`
4. Have an `edge_reason` (why the edge exists) and `kill_condition` (what invalidates it) on every signal

## The Three Questions Test
Before adding ANY signal, it must answer:
1. **Why does this edge exist?** (behavioral bias, information lag, mechanical flow, regulatory constraint)
2. **Why hasn't it been arbitraged away?** (capacity, capital requirement, holding period, execution difficulty)
3. **What kills this edge?** (regime change, crowding, data loss, regulatory change)

## Stop-Losses
Always ATR-based via `backend.adaptive.stops.compute_stop()`. Never fixed percentage.

## Position Sizing
Always via `backend.adaptive.kelly_adaptive.compute_adaptive_kelly()`. Never equal-weight.

## Strategy Registry
Strategies are enabled/disabled via config flags (`ENABLE_STAT_ARB`, etc.).
Paid-data strategies (flow_imbalance, gap_reversion intraday) degrade gracefully when data unavailable.
